WEBVTT

01:40.460 --> 01:45.950
[Speed and Love]

01:46.390 --> 01:48.720
[Episode 25]

01:50.800 --> 01:52.060
Still running a fever?

02:45.680 --> 02:46.680
Feel it yourself.

03:14.470 --> 03:15.190
Let's go in.

03:39.780 --> 03:41.310
Moonlight. Not on the menu.

03:43.050 --> 03:43.720
Try it.

04:11.750 --> 04:13.510
Watching them prepare crabs

04:14.470 --> 04:16.480
reminds me of our childhood.

04:18.950 --> 04:20.550
Every Mid-Autumn Festival,

04:21.070 --> 04:22.950
Mom would buy crabs for us too.

04:26.880 --> 04:28.280
I still have a box at home.

04:40.230 --> 04:41.890
You're taking me to your home?

05:09.920 --> 05:11.320
You've been here before?

05:27.700 --> 05:28.380
Let's go.

05:53.530 --> 05:55.390
Do you have any women's slippers?

05:57.710 --> 05:59.110
The ones Dr. Julia wears.

05:59.420 --> 06:00.950
Would you like to wear them?

06:03.320 --> 06:04.920
I'll stick with these, then.

06:12.920 --> 06:14.190
Did you

06:14.630 --> 06:16.030
buy this place or rent it?

06:17.560 --> 06:18.270
I bought it.

06:19.510 --> 06:20.800
Looks like you're doing pretty well.

06:20.800 --> 06:21.950
Then you wouldn't mind

06:21.950 --> 06:23.550
if I just look around, right?

06:26.550 --> 06:27.230
Wait.

06:29.480 --> 06:31.080
Are you hiding someone here?

06:32.440 --> 06:34.640
Didn't you already run into one before?

06:37.600 --> 06:39.800
Dr. Julia looks really good for her age.

06:40.120 --> 06:42.560
She's over 50 but looks like she's 30.

06:42.710 --> 06:44.390
I thought she was your wife.

06:46.880 --> 06:48.810
You've got quite the imagination.

06:49.040 --> 06:50.040
I'm going in then.

06:58.950 --> 07:00.210
Just messing with you.

07:01.270 --> 07:02.730
I grew up with your pranks.

07:14.680 --> 07:15.600
Let me help too.

07:16.950 --> 07:17.680
You know how?

07:20.880 --> 07:22.070
I have to.

07:22.390 --> 07:24.440
No one has taken care of me
all these years.

07:24.440 --> 07:26.900
I'd have starved to death
if I couldn't cook.

07:34.750 --> 07:35.920
No one to take care of you?

07:35.920 --> 07:36.880
No one has

07:37.440 --> 07:39.040
pursued you all these years?

07:39.830 --> 07:40.680
Quite a few.

07:45.240 --> 07:47.040
Then why didn't you date anyone?

07:48.390 --> 07:49.070
I did.

07:49.270 --> 07:51.600
One of them was even in a rock band.

07:51.920 --> 07:52.680
Once,

07:52.800 --> 07:54.750
he took me to a remote mountain area

07:54.880 --> 07:56.540
where there was a frozen lake.

07:56.710 --> 07:57.710
He jumped right in

07:57.750 --> 07:59.280
and wanted me to jump in too.

08:06.800 --> 08:07.600
Seriously?

08:07.880 --> 08:10.000
Will you believe anything I say?

08:11.170 --> 08:12.820
Running out of things to talk about, huh?

08:12.820 --> 08:14.620
No, I've got plenty more.

08:20.960 --> 08:23.070
[Sanlai]

08:23.630 --> 08:24.390
Brandy.

08:25.440 --> 08:27.360
If you're not coming over,
we'll come to you.

08:27.360 --> 08:28.390
About two hours.

08:28.750 --> 08:31.150
It's no fun being alone
during the holiday.

08:31.150 --> 08:32.480
I'm not alone right now.

08:32.700 --> 08:33.380
Sorry,

08:33.909 --> 08:35.370
I forgot about Lightning.

08:35.480 --> 08:37.809
Anyway, don't worry. We'll be there soon.

08:44.670 --> 08:45.580
Sorry, dude.

08:45.660 --> 08:47.860
I'm hanging up now. Sorry to bother you.

08:54.630 --> 08:55.960
My lifelong reputation

08:56.480 --> 08:57.530
is ruined by you.

08:59.510 --> 09:01.510
I'll take responsibility for that.

09:05.200 --> 09:06.800
What would you like to drink?

09:08.080 --> 09:09.610
I'll have some of your wine.

09:10.840 --> 09:11.840
You want to drink?

09:13.630 --> 09:14.390
Can't I?

09:33.270 --> 09:34.330
What will you have?

09:36.240 --> 09:37.440
I'll just have water.

09:56.390 --> 09:57.320
How's your mom?

10:00.960 --> 10:02.620
Her health has improved a lot.

10:03.200 --> 10:04.270
All these years in Canada,

10:04.270 --> 10:06.510
I've been taking her
to follow-up appointments.

10:06.510 --> 10:08.960
She's gradually gotten used to life there.

10:42.150 --> 10:42.980
For me?

10:54.840 --> 10:56.750
I like to dip my crab in vinegar.

11:04.390 --> 11:05.650
After all these years,

11:06.360 --> 11:08.390
he's still as attentive as ever.

11:25.320 --> 11:26.520
Don't drink too much.

11:27.670 --> 11:30.470
Don't expect me to take care of you
if you get drunk.

11:32.860 --> 11:34.460
You used to say that too.

11:55.390 --> 11:56.270
Zhao.

11:58.030 --> 11:58.690
Brother...

11:58.930 --> 11:59.520
No.

12:00.320 --> 12:01.080
Jin Zhao.

12:01.960 --> 12:02.910
Considering you went through

12:02.910 --> 12:05.110
something this big without telling me,

12:05.200 --> 12:05.930
I've decided

12:06.200 --> 12:08.200
to disown you as my sibling.

12:09.430 --> 12:10.150
Cheers.

12:24.550 --> 12:26.880
You know I'm still an intern, right?

12:29.430 --> 12:31.550
The internship salary is really low.

12:31.790 --> 12:33.880
Every month, I have to pay for rent,

12:34.080 --> 12:35.740
water, electricity, and gas.

12:35.880 --> 12:37.320
When I was in school,

12:37.630 --> 12:39.330
Mom always supported me financially.

12:39.330 --> 12:40.780
Now that I'm on my own,

12:40.800 --> 12:43.230
I can't keep asking her for money.

12:44.030 --> 12:46.560
I feel like I can barely
afford to eat anymore.

12:49.390 --> 12:51.050
You want to borrow some money?

12:52.880 --> 12:54.280
I want to move in with you.

12:55.030 --> 12:55.630
No way.

12:56.880 --> 12:58.320
Why not?

12:59.100 --> 13:01.010
You're living alone anyway.

13:01.030 --> 13:02.020
If I move in,

13:02.050 --> 13:04.080
I can help with your living expenses.

13:04.080 --> 13:06.010
And although I'm just an intern now

13:06.030 --> 13:07.050
and don't make much,

13:07.050 --> 13:08.450
once I become permanent,

13:08.480 --> 13:10.750
I'll make more, and I can scrimp and save

13:10.770 --> 13:12.900
to contribute to household expenses.

13:13.080 --> 13:14.610
Thanks for your kind offer.

13:14.750 --> 13:17.010
But who knows who'll be supporting whom?

13:18.430 --> 13:19.390
No.

13:19.670 --> 13:21.240
Zhao, hear me out.

13:21.240 --> 13:22.500
That roommate of mine—

13:22.960 --> 13:25.050
he disappears every night

13:25.080 --> 13:27.510
and always plays weird music in the room.

13:27.510 --> 13:29.270
It really affects my work.

13:29.840 --> 13:32.350
I honestly just want to
move somewhere else.

13:33.000 --> 13:35.060
You haven't changed your old habits.

13:35.080 --> 13:37.880
Once you come over,
you cling to me and won't leave.

13:40.480 --> 13:42.340
I'm not clinging to other people.

13:54.140 --> 13:55.600
When I was sending Jiang Mu off just now,

13:55.600 --> 13:56.750
I told her straight—

13:57.750 --> 13:58.880
if you don't want her

13:59.390 --> 14:00.920
or if she's not happy there,

14:01.560 --> 14:03.160
come back, and I'll take her.

14:04.550 --> 14:05.680
Guess what she said?

14:07.840 --> 14:08.790
She said you

14:09.290 --> 14:10.690
would never abandon her.

14:27.150 --> 14:28.950
You've really made up your mind?

14:29.430 --> 14:31.490
When her mom was pregnant with her...

14:34.030 --> 14:35.830
her mom's health was never good.

14:36.960 --> 14:38.420
She was born prematurely,

14:38.600 --> 14:39.600
at eight months.

14:42.990 --> 14:44.990
She weighed just over 4 jin at birth.

14:46.460 --> 14:47.380
Her dad and I

14:48.490 --> 14:51.490
watched her lying in the incubator
through the glass.

14:56.030 --> 14:57.560
I thought to myself then...

14:59.610 --> 15:00.780
such a tiny baby,

15:01.790 --> 15:03.120
could we keep her alive?

15:05.270 --> 15:06.600
So when we were kids,

15:07.480 --> 15:08.750
whenever possible,

15:09.370 --> 15:10.630
I always gave in to her.

15:12.600 --> 15:13.800
Because I always felt

15:15.970 --> 15:18.370
it was already a miracle
that she was alive.

15:20.600 --> 15:22.000
She was picky about food,

15:22.670 --> 15:23.730
ate very little...

15:25.910 --> 15:27.910
and always caught colds and fevers.

15:28.150 --> 15:29.480
Every change of season,

15:29.960 --> 15:31.320
we'd take her to the hospital.

15:31.320 --> 15:32.380
She cried a lot too.

15:33.550 --> 15:35.120
Even a tiny bug...

15:37.630 --> 15:39.230
would frighten her to tears.

15:40.510 --> 15:42.640
Then she'd reach out for me to hold her.

15:45.860 --> 15:47.390
But she was easy to comfort.

15:51.450 --> 15:52.450
Just distract her

15:53.080 --> 15:55.740
and talk about something else,
and she'd smile.

15:55.880 --> 15:57.680
When I was little, I thought that

15:58.510 --> 16:00.510
if she ever wanted to get married...

16:04.630 --> 16:07.160
she should find someone
who understands her,

16:08.270 --> 16:09.630
knows her temperament,

16:11.850 --> 16:12.780
can comfort her,

16:13.480 --> 16:15.210
and knows what she likes to eat,

16:16.630 --> 16:17.830
what she doesn't eat,

16:18.510 --> 16:19.510
what she fears...

16:22.000 --> 16:23.060
and what she hates.

16:30.210 --> 16:32.120
If she ever ended up with someone

16:33.480 --> 16:34.790
who made her suffer,

16:37.150 --> 16:38.880
I'd beat that bastard to death.

16:48.430 --> 16:49.150
Sanlai.

16:51.920 --> 16:53.710
I can't keep her by my side.

16:58.080 --> 17:00.880
I can't let suffer because of me,
even a little bit.

17:03.000 --> 17:04.800
I can't make her life difficult.

17:16.280 --> 17:17.839
I can't be that bastard.

17:48.120 --> 17:50.520
The moon is so round
and beautiful tonight.

17:53.600 --> 17:55.280
Look over there. Over there.

18:09.120 --> 18:10.520
Let me ask you something.

18:13.710 --> 18:15.440
When you went back last time...

18:19.230 --> 18:21.690
Jin Qiang didn't give you
my contact info...

18:24.390 --> 18:25.080
right?

18:27.560 --> 18:28.730
He said

18:29.150 --> 18:31.210
you haven't been back for many years.

18:38.360 --> 18:40.120
You two wouldn't have

18:41.000 --> 18:43.000
conspired to deceive me, would you?

18:55.150 --> 18:56.950
Why aren't you saying anything?

19:03.040 --> 19:04.370
The sun shines by day...

19:09.190 --> 19:10.390
and the moon by night.

19:14.760 --> 19:16.420
The sun and moon alternate...

19:20.230 --> 19:21.360
never to meet again.

19:26.950 --> 19:28.080
What does that mean?

19:33.380 --> 19:35.780
That's what I've learned over these years.

19:37.390 --> 19:38.590
The sun shines by day,

19:39.080 --> 19:40.280
and the moon by night.

19:40.880 --> 19:42.080
The sun and moon alternate,

19:41.210 --> 19:46.030
♪ Forgotten between the rearview mirror ♪

19:43.360 --> 19:44.670
never to meet again.

19:48.360 --> 19:53.740
♪ Seeing your long unseen face
on that rainy night ♪

19:56.070 --> 20:01.550
♪ Counting backwards to
the unfulfilled promises ♪

20:03.080 --> 20:08.740
♪ The heart that is still beating
hasn't said goodbye yet ♪

20:09.230 --> 20:11.340
You said you'd wait for me to grow up.

20:09.670 --> 20:12.520
♪ Meeting again after many years ♪

20:13.010 --> 20:15.920
♪ The coffee is too sour and bitter;
I'm greedy for something sweet ♪

20:17.060 --> 20:19.690
♪ Who will circle around the line
bordering the thoughts? ♪

20:20.050 --> 20:24.180
♪ Stupidly,
I refuse to believe there's an end ♪

20:23.710 --> 20:25.100
Does that still count?

20:24.950 --> 20:26.940
♪ I must ♪

20:26.960 --> 20:30.780
♪ Continue to love,
between the sun and the moon ♪

20:30.800 --> 20:34.210
♪ Even in pain,
we indulge in the iron-like vows ♪

20:32.190 --> 20:34.670
What does it matter
if everyone is against us?

20:34.420 --> 20:35.940
♪ Willingly ♪

20:36.370 --> 20:38.060
I'm already 26.

20:38.560 --> 20:41.780
♪ At this moment ♪

20:42.000 --> 20:45.440
♪ I run towards you
before the night falls ♪

20:42.230 --> 20:45.470
I can take responsibility
for my own choices.

20:45.460 --> 20:49.980
♪ Don't ask about the past;
just bet on tomorrow ♪

20:50.020 --> 20:53.190
♪ Those dreams and longings ♪

21:11.680 --> 21:17.410
♪ I really want to fill
the void of regret ♪

21:16.470 --> 21:17.880
You said last time

21:18.650 --> 21:21.170
♪ My longing has left the bow ♪

21:18.840 --> 21:21.190
that next time we meet,
you'd let me hug you as much as I want.

21:21.190 --> 21:25.090
♪ Shooting out into the horizon ♪

21:21.880 --> 21:24.480
I've already held back a lot
the last few times.

21:25.430 --> 21:28.340
♪ Meeting again after many years ♪

21:28.710 --> 21:30.150
I wasn't asking you to let go of me.

21:28.810 --> 21:31.580
♪ The coffee is too sour;
I'm greedy for something sweet ♪

21:33.010 --> 21:35.640
♪ Who will circle around the line
bordering the thoughts? ♪

21:33.190 --> 21:35.050
Let me turn around and look at you,

21:35.230 --> 21:35.900
okay?

21:36.000 --> 21:40.130
♪ Stupidly,
I refuse to believe there's an end ♪

21:40.900 --> 21:42.890
♪ I must ♪

21:42.910 --> 21:46.730
♪ Continue to love,
between the sun and the moon ♪

21:46.750 --> 21:50.160
♪ Even in pain,
we indulge in the iron-like vows ♪

21:50.370 --> 21:51.890
♪ Willingly ♪

21:54.510 --> 21:57.730
♪ At this moment ♪

21:57.950 --> 22:01.390
♪ I run towards you
before the night falls ♪

22:01.410 --> 22:05.930
♪ Don't ask about the past;
just bet on tomorrow ♪

22:05.970 --> 22:09.140
♪ Those dreams and longings ♪

22:06.950 --> 22:08.350
Let me ask you something.

22:10.710 --> 22:12.560
If I really married someone else...

22:11.090 --> 22:13.290
♪ Look at the days that have passed ♪

22:13.480 --> 22:17.240
♪ Those were yesterday's youth ♪

22:15.140 --> 22:16.540
would you be okay with it?

22:18.040 --> 22:21.430
♪ Look at the people
parting in the crowd ♪

22:21.520 --> 22:22.990
I'm not as rational as you are.

22:21.730 --> 22:25.340
♪ They used to love each other the most ♪

22:24.880 --> 22:26.390
I can't be like you,

22:25.370 --> 22:28.000
♪ Look at what the vast world wants ♪

22:26.470 --> 22:27.800
thinking of everything

22:28.040 --> 22:29.520
and considering everyone's feelings.

22:28.310 --> 22:32.390
♪ It's nothing but a fairytale ♪

22:30.710 --> 22:31.710
I only know

22:32.520 --> 22:34.190
that things will work out in the end.

22:32.750 --> 22:36.140
♪ It's always the broken up couple ♪

22:35.840 --> 22:38.120
If I really ended up marrying a bad man—

22:36.520 --> 22:39.390
♪ Who reunite amidst love, hate,
and separation ♪

22:39.190 --> 22:40.120
as I said,

22:39.670 --> 22:41.640
♪ I must ♪

22:40.520 --> 22:42.950
someone who takes my money
to buy equipment, finds other women,

22:42.050 --> 22:45.870
♪ Continue to love,
between the sun and the moon ♪

22:43.430 --> 22:44.430
beats me,

22:44.430 --> 22:45.890
and emotionally abuses me—

22:45.890 --> 22:49.300
♪ Even in pain,
we indulge in the iron-like vows ♪

22:46.320 --> 22:48.280
you think I'd be happy then?

22:49.510 --> 22:51.030
♪ Willingly ♪

22:52.520 --> 22:53.760
Have you thought about the fact that...

22:53.650 --> 22:56.870
♪ At this moment ♪

22:56.910 --> 22:58.150
by giving me up...

22:57.090 --> 23:00.530
♪ I run towards you
before the night falls ♪

23:00.550 --> 23:02.040
♪ Don't ask about the past ♪

23:00.560 --> 23:02.470
you're also gambling with my future?

23:02.070 --> 23:05.070
♪ Just bet on tomorrow ♪

23:05.100 --> 23:08.160
♪ Those dreams and longings ♪

23:05.360 --> 23:06.620
After all these years,

23:08.190 --> 23:12.460
♪ The trails overlap again ♪

23:09.230 --> 23:10.960
I still haven't forgotten you.

23:15.980 --> 23:17.180
After all these years

23:18.780 --> 23:21.380
of drifting
and crossing paths with others...

23:24.220 --> 23:25.850
I still only love you.

23:31.470 --> 23:32.520
What should I do?

23:34.020 --> 23:34.930
Jin Zhao.

23:36.360 --> 23:37.520
Tell me,

23:38.840 --> 23:40.080
what should I do?

24:00.100 --> 24:03.210
♪ I leave after your curtain call ♪

24:00.280 --> 24:01.350
Say something.

24:05.860 --> 24:09.050
♪ I ask the tired bird ♪

24:09.840 --> 24:12.900
♪ About your news ♪

24:15.160 --> 24:18.810
♪ You're too serious in
both your passion and silence ♪

24:21.130 --> 24:26.310
♪ That's why you're always
covered in scars ♪

24:27.960 --> 24:31.560
♪ If darkness can stop the pain ♪

24:31.870 --> 24:37.060
♪ I'll let you sleep a bit longer ♪

24:38.550 --> 24:42.560
♪ I'll stay by your side tonight ♪

24:45.440 --> 24:50.560
♪ I want to meet the dusk with you ♪

24:50.920 --> 24:54.800
♪ Then stay with me until dawn ♪

24:55.580 --> 25:01.610
♪ Our moment together
feels like a lifetime ♪

25:02.070 --> 25:05.720
♪ Your remaining warmth before dawn ♪

25:06.200 --> 25:10.310
♪ Is enough for me to sink in soberly ♪

25:10.650 --> 25:14.810
♪ But I'm still waiting
for every dawn and dusk ♪

25:14.830 --> 25:18.770
♪ To run towards you again ♪

25:18.790 --> 25:26.310
♪ Even if I hug you for a moment ♪

25:29.630 --> 25:30.390
Don't cry.

25:33.600 --> 25:34.710
When you cry,

25:36.230 --> 25:37.890
I'm completely defenseless.

25:42.790 --> 25:47.520
♪ Perhaps the tides have carried
all the echoes away ♪

25:48.900 --> 25:54.290
♪ How could you not hear me at all? ♪

25:55.330 --> 25:59.340
♪ Every time I see you ♪

25:59.510 --> 26:04.210
♪ You take a part of my soul ♪

26:06.000 --> 26:09.960
♪ And longing slips in ♪

26:10.210 --> 26:14.450
♪ I want to meet the dusk with you ♪

26:14.520 --> 26:18.290
♪ Then stay with me until dawn ♪

26:14.970 --> 26:17.230
[Radiology CT scan report]

26:18.930 --> 26:24.010
♪ Our moment together
feels like a lifetime ♪

26:19.280 --> 26:20.360
Mu, listen to me.

26:22.040 --> 26:24.240
It's not that I don't want to be with you.

26:25.640 --> 26:29.280
♪ Your remaining warmth before dawn ♪

26:27.950 --> 26:29.280
It's just that I feel...

26:29.390 --> 26:33.780
♪ Is enough for me to sink in soberly ♪

26:33.230 --> 26:34.430
I feel I may not be able to

26:33.850 --> 26:35.850
♪ But I'm still waiting ♪

26:34.430 --> 26:36.230
be there for you through everything
you want to do in life.

26:36.130 --> 26:37.780
♪ For every dawn and dusk ♪

26:37.800 --> 26:41.730
♪ To run towards you again ♪

26:38.410 --> 26:41.010
You can ignore
what people around you think...

26:42.110 --> 26:45.750
♪ Can I hold you in my arms? ♪

26:42.890 --> 26:44.420
or what your parents think,

26:46.760 --> 26:47.880
but I can't.

26:46.810 --> 26:48.810
♪ Can you hear me ♪

26:48.840 --> 26:50.650
♪ Your heart also aches, right? ♪

26:50.230 --> 26:51.950
I need to be responsible for your future.

26:50.680 --> 26:54.390
♪ Those days and nights were not a waste ♪

26:54.410 --> 27:00.330
♪ How long will it take to answer ♪

26:56.910 --> 26:58.910
I'll send my latest medical reports

27:00.120 --> 27:02.050
and rehabilitation instructions

27:02.150 --> 27:03.320
to your email.

27:03.420 --> 27:07.650
♪ Meet the dusk with you ♪

27:05.990 --> 27:07.850
I don't want you to suffer with me.

27:08.140 --> 27:11.910
♪ Then stay with me until dawn ♪

27:08.600 --> 27:11.860
Think it through carefully
before you give me your answer.

27:12.550 --> 27:17.630
♪ Our moment together
feels like a lifetime ♪

27:12.950 --> 27:14.480
Don't make me wait too long.

27:19.260 --> 27:22.900
♪ Your remaining warmth before dawn ♪

27:23.020 --> 27:27.410
♪ Is enough for me to sink in soberly ♪

27:27.470 --> 27:29.470
♪ But I'm still waiting ♪

27:29.750 --> 27:31.400
♪ For every dawn and dusk ♪

27:31.430 --> 27:35.350
♪ To run towards you again ♪

27:35.730 --> 27:39.400
♪ Until I can embrace you ♪

27:37.670 --> 27:38.670
Dr. Julia,

27:38.990 --> 27:41.230
I've received Jin Zhao's medical reports.

27:41.230 --> 27:42.990
Could you go through them
with me in detail?

27:41.610 --> 27:44.900
♪ For a lifetime ♪

27:44.710 --> 27:45.630
That accident

27:45.760 --> 27:48.360
initially caused systemic damage
to his body.

27:48.880 --> 27:50.080
There was compression of the brain tissue,

27:50.080 --> 27:51.840
which led to a period of coma.

27:52.880 --> 27:55.560
Additionally, he suffered
multiple fractures throughout his body.

27:55.560 --> 27:57.630
During the long rehabilitation process,

27:57.630 --> 27:59.360
he often experienced local swelling

27:59.360 --> 28:00.280
and joint pain,

28:00.630 --> 28:02.430
resulting in limited mobility.

28:02.630 --> 28:05.160
Later, his muscle strength
began to decline.

28:06.520 --> 28:07.710
For him,

28:08.040 --> 28:09.670
recovery is a slow process,

28:10.320 --> 28:12.910
and we need to be with him
every step of the way.

28:14.840 --> 28:15.360
Okay,

28:15.840 --> 28:16.640
I understand.

28:29.280 --> 28:31.920
[Observatory]

28:32.470 --> 28:33.120
Jiang Mu.

28:36.960 --> 28:37.920
What's this?

28:37.950 --> 28:39.080
I have a favor to ask.

28:39.950 --> 28:40.910
Tomorrow, we need to host several

28:40.910 --> 28:43.360
visitors from other provinces for a tour
of the observatory.

28:43.360 --> 28:44.470
The leadership wants

28:44.470 --> 28:45.430
someone with a good presence,

28:45.430 --> 28:47.080
as they will represent
our institute's image as well.

28:47.080 --> 28:48.740
I immediately thought of you.

28:48.880 --> 28:51.010
How about it? Can you help me tomorrow?

28:51.190 --> 28:51.990
No problem.

28:52.520 --> 28:53.430
It's settled then.

28:53.430 --> 28:54.560
I'll head off first.

29:11.910 --> 29:13.280
How's that?
Pretty thoughtful of me, right?

29:13.280 --> 29:14.560
I know you've been swamped lately.

29:14.560 --> 29:16.280
Thought I'd pull you out
for some fresh air.

29:16.280 --> 29:17.360
Thanks a lot.

29:17.670 --> 29:19.520
Don't mention it.
The leaders will be here shortly.

29:19.520 --> 29:20.710
The building we're visiting now

29:20.710 --> 29:22.110
was constructed in 1929.

29:22.150 --> 29:23.150
It has a long history

29:23.150 --> 29:25.600
and is our country's
first modern observatory.

29:25.600 --> 29:27.150
Located on the peak of Purple Mountain,

29:27.150 --> 29:29.470
it embodies
a strong traditional Chinese aesthetic.

29:29.470 --> 29:30.470
Next, we'll

29:30.800 --> 29:31.910
visit the summit.

29:32.800 --> 29:34.230
Here we have
the 60-centimeter reflecting telescope

29:34.230 --> 29:36.080
at the summit of Purple Mountain.

29:36.080 --> 29:37.470
This reflecting telescope

29:37.470 --> 29:38.760
dates back to 1934.

29:39.280 --> 29:40.410
Its focal length...

29:41.520 --> 29:43.380
Let's go inside for a closer look.

29:45.200 --> 29:46.650
[Jin Zhao]

29:53.560 --> 29:54.880
When do you get off work?

29:54.880 --> 29:57.190
I'm showing some visitors around
the observatory.

29:57.190 --> 29:58.920
It'll be over in a little while.

29:59.520 --> 30:01.120
Then carry on with your work.

30:04.360 --> 30:04.990
Jiang Mu.

30:06.600 --> 30:07.950
They have other plans for tonight.

30:07.950 --> 30:10.410
We just need to see them off
to their vehicle.

30:10.740 --> 30:12.870
Want to have hot pot together tonight?

30:13.150 --> 30:14.350
I already have plans.

30:15.860 --> 30:16.660
Alright then.

30:17.330 --> 30:17.720
Let's go.

30:17.720 --> 30:18.250
Let's go.

30:24.040 --> 30:25.630
Listen, don't always
bury yourself in work.

30:25.630 --> 30:29.160
You're not getting any younger.
Consider finding a boyfriend.

30:31.520 --> 30:32.710
Why are you here?

30:34.710 --> 30:35.550
Didn't I tell you to wait for me

30:35.550 --> 30:38.550
-at the foot of the mountain?
-I wanted to come see you.

30:42.920 --> 30:44.180
How did you get up here?

30:45.050 --> 30:45.880
By cable car.

30:49.000 --> 30:52.460
Why are you making such a fuss
about him coming up the mountain?

30:53.710 --> 30:54.670
Who is this?

30:55.360 --> 30:56.470
My name is Gu Zhijie.

30:56.470 --> 30:57.630
I'm Jiang Mu's

30:57.910 --> 30:58.910
half-colleague?

31:02.280 --> 31:03.120
And this is?

31:03.390 --> 31:04.990
My ex-boyfriend of one week.

31:05.910 --> 31:07.370
I've heard a lot about you.

31:08.190 --> 31:09.950
What do you mean by "half-colleague"?

31:09.950 --> 31:11.280
I'm Jiang Mu's senior from school.

31:11.280 --> 31:12.560
Although we don't work together,

31:12.560 --> 31:15.020
I kind of tricked her into
coming to Nanjing.

31:15.120 --> 31:16.550
We're all in the same field,

31:16.550 --> 31:18.470
so we're half-colleagues.

31:22.060 --> 31:24.390
Qin and I will
see the leaders off tonight.

31:24.470 --> 31:26.560
You're really not
coming to dinner tonight?

31:26.560 --> 31:27.910
I'll call you later.

31:28.540 --> 31:29.090
Okay.

31:29.560 --> 31:31.020
Then I'll get back to work.

31:37.510 --> 31:38.510
Half-colleague.

31:41.540 --> 31:43.270
Is this your first time up here?

31:46.080 --> 31:47.480
Want me to give you a tour?

31:48.800 --> 31:50.330
If it's convenient for you.

31:50.600 --> 31:52.840
Convenient or not, you're already here.

31:52.840 --> 31:55.100
Wouldn't it be a waste not to look around?

31:56.430 --> 31:57.490
I already told you.

31:58.280 --> 31:59.480
I just came to see you.

32:01.150 --> 32:02.280
To see me?

32:03.430 --> 32:04.960
So, what have you observed?

32:10.560 --> 32:11.560
I came to see...

32:12.880 --> 32:14.540
if I've scared you away again.

32:18.910 --> 32:20.800
And what's your conclusion?

32:32.520 --> 32:34.080
This celestial globe before us

32:34.080 --> 32:35.360
is cast in bronze

32:35.470 --> 32:36.520
and can rotate.

32:36.910 --> 32:38.330
It's about three chi in diameter

32:38.330 --> 32:39.190
and is embedded with

32:39.190 --> 32:41.080
1,449 bronze pins,

32:41.320 --> 32:42.520
representing the stars

32:42.520 --> 32:43.920
visible to the naked eye.

32:47.120 --> 32:47.910
Is this ring

32:48.190 --> 32:49.390
the meridian circle?

32:51.280 --> 32:52.320
That's right.

32:52.880 --> 32:55.230
Mr. Visitor, you know your astronomy.

32:57.370 --> 32:58.170
Just a little.

33:05.450 --> 33:06.710
This is a celestial globe,

33:06.710 --> 33:09.390
called Huntianyi or Hunxiang
in ancient times.

33:10.040 --> 33:11.080
Back in the Eastern Han Dynasty,

33:11.080 --> 33:12.230
there was a star-gazing boy

33:12.230 --> 33:14.090
named Zhang Heng who improved it,

33:14.090 --> 33:14.880
giving it the function

33:14.880 --> 33:17.410
of demonstrating celestial body movements.

33:17.990 --> 33:18.950
My work focuses on

33:18.950 --> 33:20.600
the dynamics of

33:20.600 --> 33:22.400
multi-body celestial systems.

33:24.120 --> 33:25.040
Come to think of it,

33:25.040 --> 33:28.220
you were actually the one
who first introduced me to all this.

33:28.220 --> 33:29.680
Have you been busy lately?

33:44.700 --> 33:46.100
Let me ask you something.

33:47.910 --> 33:49.320
If I really had a fiancé

33:49.600 --> 33:50.930
who loved playing games

33:51.120 --> 33:52.600
and chasing women,

33:53.020 --> 33:54.020
what would you do?

33:58.290 --> 33:59.490
Do you want the truth?

33:59.710 --> 34:00.390
Of course.

34:02.430 --> 34:03.890
I'd make you willingly...

34:05.420 --> 34:07.020
dump him before the wedding.

34:10.389 --> 34:12.159
Willingly dump him?

34:12.380 --> 34:13.710
And be with you instead?

34:30.679 --> 34:32.480
Let me ask you another question.

34:33.810 --> 34:35.810
What if I really got scared off

34:36.989 --> 34:38.449
after seeing that report?

34:44.949 --> 34:46.159
Then I should...

34:47.030 --> 34:50.290
still be able to catch the last cable car
down the mountain.

35:07.200 --> 35:08.070
So...

35:13.350 --> 35:14.810
have you made up your mind?

35:16.800 --> 35:18.730
I want to take you somewhere first.

36:20.590 --> 36:21.760
Do you see that?

36:30.550 --> 36:31.880
Every year at this time,

36:32.800 --> 36:34.200
the Earth's orbit around the Sun

36:34.200 --> 36:36.030
and the Moon's orbit around the Earth

36:36.030 --> 36:37.430
undergo slight changes.

36:39.030 --> 36:40.160
The moon and sun

36:40.280 --> 36:42.480
appear simultaneously on the horizon,

36:42.530 --> 36:45.990
creating the phenomenon
of the sun and moon shining together.

36:52.360 --> 36:53.890
The sun and moon alternate.

36:54.240 --> 36:56.430
Even natural laws aren't absolute,

36:58.580 --> 36:59.850
let alone people.

37:12.690 --> 37:13.650
Do you get...

37:15.890 --> 37:17.410
what I'm trying to say?

37:26.420 --> 37:27.620
The sun shines by day,

37:29.760 --> 37:30.960
and the moon by night.

37:33.590 --> 37:35.390
The sun and moon shine together.

37:37.420 --> 37:38.750
You and I

37:40.810 --> 37:42.200
will never be apart.

37:49.470 --> 37:51.240
This is my answer.
